results.title: The Top 25 Economies in the World
results.content: The U.S., China, Germany, Japan, and India are some of the top economies in the world based on gross domestic product (GDP). The United States economy is the largest in the world as measured by nominal GDP. South Korea is the 12th-largest economy in the world by GDP. Australia combines a relatively open domestic economy with an extensive network of free trade agreements with trading partners all around the Asia-Pacific Rim. This works to the advantage of Australia’s abundant natural resources and agricultural export industries; however, it has also left Australia vulnerable to swings in world commodity demand and prices in energy (coal and natural gas), metals (iron ore and gold), and agricultural products (beef and sheep products).38 Spain's GDP makes it the 14th-largest economy in the world.
